<h1>@HI{{nagara}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<p>
<ol>
<li> @V2{{}} <strong>@HI{{nagara}}</strong>, V2
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

This sentence pattern means that two actions (V1 and V2) are being performed at the same time.
The action in the main clause, V2, is the more emphasised of the two.
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<strong>@HI{{nagara}}</strong> expresses the fact that an action occurs at the same time as another action.
The action marked by <strong>@HI{{nagara}}</strong> is the secondary action.
<p></p>

If the subjects of the two verbs are different, <strong>@HI{{nagara}}</strong> cannot be used.
A possible alternative in this case would be @HI{{aida}}.
<p></p>

